Copy your GitHub App's private key (a PEM-encoded RSA key) into a file
named `github-app-key.pem` in this directory.

You can download it from:
  GitHub > Settings > Developer settings > GitHub Apps > <your app>
  > Private keys > Generate a private key

The file is mounted read-only into the worker containers at
/run/secrets/github-app-key.pem and referenced from dev.toml.

The .gitignore in the repo root excludes *.pem so the real key won't
accidentally be committed.
